<title>Standards</title>
<para id="fs-idm469287168"><emphasis effect="bold">Topic</emphasis>: 8.12 Youth Culture of the 1960s</para>
<para id="fs-idm472507872"><emphasis effect="bold">Theme</emphasis>: ARC American and Regional Culture</para>
<para id="fs-idm331903344"><emphasis effect="bold">Learning Objective</emphasis>: Unit 8N Explain how and why opposition to existing policies and values developed and changed over the course of the 20th century</para>
<para id="fs-idm496287584"><emphasis effect="bold">Historical Development</emphasis>: 8.1.II.B</para>
<para id="fs-idm350190016"><emphasis effect="bold">Historical Thinking Skills</emphasis>: HTS-2 Sourcing and Situation, HTS-3 Source Claims and Evidence, HTS-4 Contextualization, HTS-5 Making Connections, HTS-6 Argumentation</para>
